help for heartburn during pregnancy i'm in my fourteenth week and have very severe heartburn that causes me to throw up tums don't seem to be working and i don't want to go on any medications stronger than that does anybody have a miracle cure i too have suffered from severe heartburn and indigestion a lot of the times stuff comes up when i try to burp which is not pleasant my advice stay away from things that cause heartburn to be worse chocolate caffeine tomato sauce etc give yourself at least hours after eating before laying down try to keep your upper body in an upright position gravity helps the acid to stay down tums didn't really work for me either i tried rolaids and they helped more than tums but dont eat too many of them call your doctor for any futher tips and advise Heartburn Gastroesophageal reflux disease Stomach cancer Coeliac disease Fecal incontinence Gastroparesis Caffeine Insomnia Tomato Mouth ulcer Attention-deficit hyperactivity disorder Breastfeeding Urinary incontinence Non-Hodgkin's lymphoma Folic acid Word of Wisdom Garlic Common cold Psoriasis Obstetrics Guinea pig Kevin Trudeau Crohn's disease Acne Herpes simplex virus Similarities between the Bible and the Qur'an Migraine Prostate cancer Chocolate Sleep Vitamin Clomipramine Stuttering Fancy rat Coffee Tightlacing Bipolar disorder H2-receptor antagonist Hangover Anorexia nervosa Hypoglycemia Antidepressant Osteoarthritis Chronic fatigue syndrome Dieting Cuisine of Denmark Immortality Morning sickness Childbirth Medicine Bart chalkboard gags Miscarriage Limp Bizkit Kishore Kumar Fertility awareness Pregnancy A Course In Miracles Raw food diet Cuisine of the Philippines Aerial (dance move) The Adventures of Pete & Pete Alcoholics Anonymous Diabetic retinopathy Botulism Procrastination Roe v. Wade Hormone replacement therapy (trans) Boards of Canada Time Out of Mind Hot sauce Development of Darwin's theory Diarrhea First aid Vitamin C Oral sex Rosa Parks Milton H. Erickson Shit Garfield Sandw